posts.name: 5089 Robonerds
posts.cooked:
We are using the ctre swerve generated code for our robot . When trying create paths in path planner we keep getting the message “Failed to generate trajectory. This is likely due to bad control point placement. Please adjust your control points to avoid kinks in the path.” It keeps doing this no matter where the points end up. Does anybody know how we could fix this either in the code or in the pathplanner GUI. Thank you in advance. Attached is a picture example. Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 199 KB

Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 199 KB

Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 199 KB
When we ran into this issue it was due to setting a too low speed in the configuration settings

posts.name: 5089 Robonerds
posts.cooked: where would we fix this and what value would you recommend?

In the path lanner gui go to the hamburger menu (the three lines), and in the settings gear menu, there is a module config area. Make sure it matches what you probably have in your constants.java (assuming you are using java). for us the value is 4.8 M/S

posts.name: 5089 Robonerds
posts.cooked: What is Wheel COF? we are using CTRE ’s swerve generator and don’t know what to put for that value.
That would be the wheels coefficient of friction, you would need to find that for your modules, although for what its worth, I dont think we have ever changed the default value there.

posts.name: 5089 Robonerds
posts.cooked: We just found it, our pathplanner is finally moving so thank you very much
